NAME
     set-log-attributes - sets the logging attributes for one  or
     more loggers

SYNOPSIS
     set-log-attributes [--help] [--target=target]
     attribute-name=attribute-value[:attribute-name=attribute-value]*

DESCRIPTION
     The set-log-attributes subcommand  sets  logging  attributes
     for  one  or  more  loggers.  The  attributes  you  can  set
     correspond to the  attributes  that  are  available  in  the
     logging.properties  file  for  the  domain. Depending on the
     attributes you set, a server  restart  may  or  may  not  be
     necessary.

     This subcommand is supported in remote mode only.

OPTIONS
     --help
     -?

         Displays the help text for the subcommand.

     target
         The server domain, instance, or cluster for which logger
         attributes  will  be  listed. If this option is omitted,
         attributes are listed  for  the  default  domain.  Valid
         values are:

             o    domain_name - The name of a target domain.

             o    cluster_name- The name of a target cluster.

             o    instance_name- The  name  of  a  target  server
                  instance.

OPERANDS
     attribute-name

         The fully scoped name  of  the  logging  attribute.  The
         list-log-attributes  subcommand  can be used to list the
         names of all currently defined attributes.

     attribute-value
         The value to apply to the specified attribute.

